title: TRANSFER FAIL
body:
Status: Transfer failed. You will be able to continue playing in the current region(Europe West.) Your account balance has not been debited. Your account has not been activated on the new region (Europe Nordic and East.) 

Reason:Unexpected error (9500) encountered during transfer. Please try again at a later date.

> How do i fix this? I cant transfer... and I have tried to uninstall and reinstall it. Doesnt work. I have restarted lol and my computer  a cupple of times as well.

replies.body:
Thanks friends for the reports as well as troubleshooting with me.  I've collected these details and passed the information on to interested parties.  We're looking into this to see what's going on, and I'll offer an update as soon as I can.  Hang tight!

**Update**:  Transfers have been disabled while we work towards a solution.  We'll be updating the [service status](http://status.leagueoflegends.com/#na) page with any changes on this.

**Update 2**:  Transfers look to be back up now!
Transfers were just disabled. https://status.leagueoflegends.com/#euw

Me and some friends have the same problem, trying to transfer from RU to EUW. None of us are in a club or team, I was in a team before they got removed though, not sure if that's relevant. My friends weren't in one though.
Trying to transfer from NA to EUW here, have left clubs and am not in any ranked teams but I get the same error as posted in this thread. Any advice?
Same i want to transfer from euw to eune and i get the same error . No clubs no ranked teams . Thanks in advance

You are making a lot of transfer attempts, hang on!  Taking a look into this, It seems like you're in a ranked team.  Leaving that should allow you to transfer, but make sure to go over the[ Transfer FAQ](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201751924-Account-Transfer-FAQ) to fully prepare for your departure.  Hope that helps clear things up.
I have the same problem as OP but i am not on a ranked team? what do i do?
Can you try again and let me know?  Just once is enough- you may be causing unintended issues by repeatedly trying in a short period.
Ok so i waited for about 5-10 minutes before trying again, and it is still showing the same error :(
Were you in a club or affected by the recent club issues?  If so what was the name or tag of the club you were in?

I was in 2 clubs but i left the other after the club issues, im still in the other one. The name of it is 'Naked Fire'
Edit: Were to was*
Thanks!  Do you have the name of the club that had the issues?  Also, can you leave your current club then try again?
I'll try it and report back to you!

Thank you so much!
